@page "/ControlSamples/ModalPopupExtender"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>ModalPopupExtender Component Samples</PageTitle>

<h2>ModalPopupExtender Component</h2>

<p>The <code>ModalPopupExtender</code> displays a target element as a modal popup with an overlay backdrop. It supports OK/Cancel buttons, drag support, drop shadow, and Escape key dismissal. This emulates the Ajax Control Toolkit <code>ModalPopupExtender</code>.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Note:</strong> Extender components render <strong>no HTML</strong> themselves — they attach JavaScript behavior to an existing target element identified by <code>TargetControlID</code>. This page requires <code>InteractiveServer</code> render mode for JS interop.
</div>

<hr />

<h3>1. Basic Modal Popup with OK/Cancel</h3>
<p>A button opens a modal popup panel. The user confirms with OK or dismisses with Cancel.</p>

<div data-audit-control="ModalPopupExtender-1">
    <button id="btnShowBasic" class="btn btn-primary">
        Show Modal
    </button>
    <ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShowBasic"
                        PopupControlID="pnlBasicModal"
                        OkControlID="btnBasicOk"
                        CancelControlID="btnBasicCancel"
                        BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop-demo" />

    <div id="pnlBasicModal" class="modal-popup-demo" style="display:none;">
        <h4>Confirm Action</h4>
        <p>Are you sure you want to proceed?</p>
        <div class="d-flex gap-2 justify-content-end">
            <button id="btnBasicOk" class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="HandleBasicOk">OK</button>
            <button id="btnBasicCancel" class="btn btn-secondary">Cancel</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(basicStatus))
    {
        <div class="alert alert-success mt-2">@basicStatus</div>
    }
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;!-- Web Forms (Before) --&gt;
&lt;asp:Button ID="btnShow" runat="server" Text="Show Modal" /&gt;
&lt;asp:Panel ID="pnlModal" runat="server" CssClass="modal-popup" style="display:none"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Are you sure you want to proceed?&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;asp:Button ID="btnOk" runat="server" Text="OK" /&gt;
    &lt;asp:Button ID="btnCancel" runat="server" Text="Cancel" /&gt;
&lt;/asp:Panel&gt;
&lt;ajaxToolkit:ModalPopupExtender ID="mpe1" runat="server"
    TargetControlID="btnShow" PopupControlID="pnlModal"
    OkControlID="btnOk" CancelControlID="btnCancel"
    BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop" /&gt;

&lt;!-- Blazor with BWFC (After) --&gt;
&lt;button id="btnShow"&gt;Show Modal&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;div id="pnlModal" style="display:none"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Are you sure you want to proceed?&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;button id="btnOk"&gt;OK&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button id="btnCancel"&gt;Cancel&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShow" PopupControlID="pnlModal"
                    OkControlID="btnOk" CancelControlID="btnCancel"
                    BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop" /&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>2. Modal with Custom Backdrop CSS</h3>
<p>Customize the backdrop overlay using your own CSS class for branding or visual emphasis.</p>

<div data-audit-control="ModalPopupExtender-2">
    <button id="btnShowCustom" class="btn btn-info">
        Show Modal (Custom Backdrop)
    </button>
    <ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShowCustom"
                        PopupControlID="pnlCustomModal"
                        OkControlID="btnCustomOk"
                        CancelControlID="btnCustomCancel"
                        BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop-custom" />

    <div id="pnlCustomModal" class="modal-popup-demo" style="display:none;">
        <h4>Custom Backdrop</h4>
        <p>This modal uses a tinted backdrop. The <code>BackgroundCssClass</code> controls the overlay appearance.</p>
        <div class="d-flex gap-2 justify-content-end">
            <button id="btnCustomOk" class="btn btn-info">Got It</button>
            <button id="btnCustomCancel" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Dismiss</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;!-- Use BackgroundCssClass to style the overlay --&gt;
&lt;ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShow" PopupControlID="pnlModal"
                    OkControlID="btnOk" CancelControlID="btnCancel"
                    BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop-custom" /&gt;

&lt;style&gt;
    .modal-backdrop-custom {
        background-color: rgba(0, 100, 200, 0.4);
    }
&lt;/style&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>3. Modal with Drag Support</h3>
<p>Enable <code>Drag="true"</code> to allow the user to reposition the modal popup. Use <code>PopupDragHandleControlID</code> to designate a specific drag handle.</p>

<div data-audit-control="ModalPopupExtender-3">
    <button id="btnShowDrag" class="btn btn-warning">
        Show Draggable Modal
    </button>
    <ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShowDrag"
                        PopupControlID="pnlDragModal"
                        OkControlID="btnDragClose"
                        BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop-demo"
                        Drag="true"
                        PopupDragHandleControlID="dragHandle" />

    <div id="pnlDragModal" class="modal-popup-demo" style="display:none;">
        <div id="dragHandle" class="modal-drag-handle">
            ☰ Drag me to reposition
        </div>
        <p>This modal can be dragged by its title bar. Try moving it around!</p>
        <button id="btnDragClose" class="btn btn-warning">Close</button>
    </div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShow" PopupControlID="pnlModal"
                    OkControlID="btnClose"
                    BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop"
                    Drag="true"
                    PopupDragHandleControlID="dragHandle" /&gt;

&lt;div id="pnlModal" style="display:none"&gt;
    &lt;div id="dragHandle" class="drag-handle"&gt;Drag me&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Draggable content&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;button id="btnClose"&gt;Close&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>4. Modal with Drop Shadow</h3>
<p>Set <code>DropShadow="true"</code> to add a visual shadow effect to the popup panel.</p>

<div data-audit-control="ModalPopupExtender-4">
    <button id="btnShowShadow" class="btn btn-dark">
        Show Modal (Drop Shadow)
    </button>
    <ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShowShadow"
                        PopupControlID="pnlShadowModal"
                        OkControlID="btnShadowClose"
                        BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop-demo"
                        DropShadow="true" />

    <div id="pnlShadowModal" class="modal-popup-demo" style="display:none;">
        <h4>Drop Shadow Modal</h4>
        <p>This popup has <code>DropShadow="true"</code> enabled, adding a shadow effect for visual depth.</p>
        <button id="btnShadowClose" class="btn btn-dark">Close</button>
    </div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShow" PopupControlID="pnlModal"
                    OkControlID="btnClose"
                    BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop"
                    DropShadow="true" /&gt;</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>5. Programmatic Show/Hide</h3>
<p>Use Blazor visibility state to programmatically control when the modal trigger becomes active. The extender still manages the show/hide behavior via the target button.</p>

<div data-audit-control="ModalPopupExtender-5">
    <div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-2">
        <button class="btn btn-success" @onclick="() => showTrigger = true">Enable Modal Trigger</button>
        <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" @onclick="() => showTrigger = false">Disable Modal Trigger</button>
    </div>

    @if (showTrigger)
    {
        <button id="btnShowProgrammatic" class="btn btn-success">
            Open Programmatic Modal
        </button>
        <ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShowProgrammatic"
                            PopupControlID="pnlProgrammaticModal"
                            OkControlID="btnProgrammaticOk"
                            CancelControlID="btnProgrammaticCancel"
                            BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop-demo" />
    }
    else
    {
        <span class="text-muted">Modal trigger is disabled. Click "Enable Modal Trigger" to activate.</span>
    }

    <div id="pnlProgrammaticModal" class="modal-popup-demo" style="display:none;">
        <h4>Programmatic Modal</h4>
        <p>This modal's trigger button is conditionally rendered via Blazor state.</p>
        <div class="d-flex gap-2 justify-content-end">
            <button id="btnProgrammaticOk" class="btn btn-success" @onclick="HandleProgrammaticOk">Confirm</button>
            <button id="btnProgrammaticCancel" class="btn btn-secondary">Cancel</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(programmaticStatus))
    {
        <div class="alert alert-info mt-2">@programmaticStatus</div>
    }
</div>

<pre><code>@@if (showTrigger)
{
    &lt;button id="btnShow"&gt;Open Modal&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShow"
                        PopupControlID="pnlModal"
                        OkControlID="btnOk" CancelControlID="btnCancel"
                        BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop" /&gt;
}

@@code {
    private bool showTrigger = false;
}</code></pre>

<hr />

<h3>Migration Guide: Ajax Control Toolkit to Blazor</h3>

<h4>Ajax Control Toolkit (Before)</h4>
<pre><code class="language-aspx">&lt;asp:ScriptManager ID="ScriptManager1" runat="server" /&gt;
&lt;asp:Button ID="btnShow" runat="server" Text="Show Popup" /&gt;
&lt;asp:Panel ID="pnlPopup" runat="server" CssClass="popup" style="display:none"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Modal content here&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;asp:Button ID="btnOk" runat="server" Text="OK" /&gt;
    &lt;asp:Button ID="btnCancel" runat="server" Text="Cancel" /&gt;
&lt;/asp:Panel&gt;
&lt;ajaxToolkit:ModalPopupExtender ID="ModalPopupExtender1" runat="server"
    TargetControlID="btnShow"
    PopupControlID="pnlPopup"
    OkControlID="btnOk"
    CancelControlID="btnCancel"
    BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop"
    DropShadow="true"
    Drag="true"
    PopupDragHandleControlID="pnlDragHandle" /&gt;</code></pre>

<h4>Blazor with BWFC (After)</h4>
<pre><code>&lt;button id="btnShow"&gt;Show Popup&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;div id="pnlPopup" style="display:none"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Modal content here&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;button id="btnOk"&gt;OK&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button id="btnCancel"&gt;Cancel&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ModalPopupExtender TargetControlID="btnShow"
                    PopupControlID="pnlPopup"
                    OkControlID="btnOk"
                    CancelControlID="btnCancel"
                    BackgroundCssClass="modal-backdrop"
                    DropShadow="true"
                    Drag="true"
                    PopupDragHandleControlID="pnlDragHandle" /&gt;</code></pre>

<h4>Migration Steps</h4>
<ol>
    <li>Remove <code>asp:ScriptManager</code> (not needed in Blazor)</li>
    <li>Replace <code>&lt;asp:Button&gt;</code> with a standard <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> element</li>
    <li>Replace <code>&lt;asp:Panel&gt;</code> with a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> (keep the same <code>id</code>)</li>
    <li>Replace <code>&lt;ajaxToolkit:ModalPopupExtender&gt;</code> with <code>&lt;ModalPopupExtender&gt;</code></li>
    <li>Keep the same property names: <code>TargetControlID</code>, <code>PopupControlID</code>, <code>OkControlID</code>, <code>CancelControlID</code>, <code>BackgroundCssClass</code></li>
    <li><code>DropShadow</code> and <code>Drag</code> properties carry over directly</li>
    <li>Ensure the page uses <code>@@rendermode InteractiveServer</code> (JS interop required)</li>
</ol>

<style>
    .modal-popup-demo {
        background: white;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 20px;
        min-width: 300px;
        max-width: 450px;
    }

    .modal-backdrop-demo {
        background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
    }

    .modal-backdrop-custom {
        background-color: rgba(0, 100, 200, 0.4);
    }

    .modal-drag-handle {
        background-color: #f0f0f0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        padding: 8px 12px;
        margin: -20px -20px 15px -20px;
        border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
        cursor: move;
        font-weight: bold;
    }
</style>

@code {
    private string basicStatus = "";
    private string programmaticStatus = "";
    private bool showTrigger = false;

    private void HandleBasicOk()
    {
        basicStatus = $"Confirmed at {DateTime.Now:h:mm:ss tt}";
    }

    private void HandleProgrammaticOk()
    {
        programmaticStatus = $"Action confirmed at {DateTime.Now:h:mm:ss tt}";
    }
}
